      "content": "thanks for the breakdown. i noticed a lot of the literature focuses on the 'trickle-down' critique, but some economists argue that the growth-focused approach is actually the most reliable way to lift the floor for everyone in the long run. do you see any empirical evidence that supports the growth-led view, or is that just considered a theoretical argument that doesn't hold up to reality?",
